What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Cellulose Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global cellulose market, which was USD 40.56 billion in 2022, would rocket up to USD 93.10 billion by 2030 and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 9.67% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030.

Cellulose is used as cellulose derivatives such as acetate, cellulose ethers, and cellulose esters. These derivatives have applications in various industries, including pharmaceuticals, food, textiles, and cosmetics. They are used as thickeners, stabilizers, emulsifiers, and film-forming agents, among other functions.

The natural source segment is expected to dominate the global cellulose market due to its sustainable and renewable nature, making it a preferred choice for environmentally conscious industries and consumers.

“Natural” dominates the source segment of the cellulose market due to its sustainable and renewable nature, making it a preferred choice for environmentally conscious industries and consumers.

